HEADWORD: Tetrameter
<hw>Te*tram"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tetrametrus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>te`tra-</grk> (see
<er>Tetra-</er>) + <?/ a measure: cf. F.
<ets>t⟦eacute⟧tram⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(GR. & Latin
Pros.)</fld> <def>A verse or line consisting of four measures, that is,
in iambic, trochaic, and anapestic verse, of eight feet; in other kinds
of verse, of four feet.</def>⟦br⟧
